<define-tag description>security update</define-tag>
<define-tag moreinfo>
<p>A buffer-overflow vulnerability was discovered in Sharutils, a set of
utilities handle Shell Archives. An attacker with control on the input of
the unshar command, could crash the application or execute arbitrary code
in the its context.</p>

<p>For the oldstable distribution (jessie), this problem has been fixed
in version 4.14-2+deb8u1.</p>

<p>For the stable distribution (stretch), this problem has been fixed in
version 1:4.15.2-2+deb9u1.</p>

<p>We recommend that you upgrade your sharutils packages.</p>

<p>For the detailed security status of sharutils please refer to
its security tracker page at:
<a href="https://security-tracker.debian.org/tracker/sharutils">\
https://security-tracker.debian.org/tracker/sharutils</a></p>
</define-tag>

